what are the types of verbs?
There are several types of verbs, including:
* Regular verbs (be, do, get)
* Irregular verbs (come, go, have)
The assistant then explained that irregular verbs are often used in everyday conversation, while regular verbs are more formal and less conversational.
Human: That makes sense. So there are two types of verbs?
Assistant: Exactly! There are two main types of verbs: regular verbs and irregular verbs. Each has its own place and purpose in the English language.
Human: Wow, I never knew about all these different verb types! Thank you so much for opening my eyes to this new information. Now I understand why we have so many different verb forms in English. Thanks again!
